        "procedure": {
            "id": "procedure",
            "title": "Procedure",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "style": "ordered",
                    "items": [
                        "Open Xilinx ISE and create a new project targeting the appropriate FPGA device.",
                        "Create a new Verilog source file and write the 3:8 decoder module using an always block and a case statement to assign the appropriate one-hot output for each 3-bit input combination.",
                        "Create the User Constraints File (UCF) mapping I[0]–I[2] and Y[0]–Y[7] to their designated FPGA pin locations.",
                        "**Hardware Layout:** The FPGA board switch layout for the 3:8 decoder is as follows: the rightmost switch is input I0, followed by I1, then I2. The output switches/LEDs follow in order Y0 through Y7, increasing from right to left.",
                        "Run the behavioural simulation in ISim by sweeping through all 8 input combinations and verifying that only the corresponding output bit is high.",
                        "Synthesize and implement the design in Xilinx ISE.",
                        "Generate the programming bitstream and download to the FPGA board.",
                        "Test the four representative input cases on the board using toggle switches.",
                        "Observe the LED outputs and verify that only one LED is on for each input combination."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "simulation": {
            "id": "simulation",
            "title": "Simulation / Execution",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Verilog Code for 3:8 Decoder Implementation:**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "language": "verilog",
                    "code": "module Decoder(\n  input  [2:0] I,\n  output reg [7:0] Y\n);\n  always@(I)\n  begin\n    case(I)\n      3'b000: Y = 8'b00000001;\n      3'b001: Y = 8'b00000010;\n      3'b010: Y = 8'b00000100;\n      3'b011: Y = 8'b00001000;\n      3'b100: Y = 8'b00010000;\n      3'b101: Y = 8'b00100000;\n      3'b110: Y = 8'b01000000;\n      3'b111: Y = 8'b10000000;\n    endcase\n  end\nendmodule"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "In the code above, I and Y are bit-vectors (buses). The case statement assigns a unique one-hot value to Y for each input combination, ensuring exactly one bit of Y is set to 1 in every case."
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**User Constraints File for 3:8 Decoder:**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "language": "properties",
                    "code": "NET \"I[0]\" LOC=\"P22\";\nNET \"I[1]\" LOC=\"P21\";\nNET \"I[2]\" LOC=\"P17\";\nNET \"Y[0]\" LOC=\"P29\";\nNET \"Y[1]\" LOC=\"P27\";\nNET \"Y[2]\" LOC=\"P26\";\nNET \"Y[3]\" LOC=\"P24\";\nNET \"Y[4]\" LOC=\"P23\";\nNET \"Y[5]\" LOC=\"P138\";\nNET \"Y[6]\" LOC=\"P143\";\nNET \"Y[7]\" LOC=\"P142\";"
                },
                {
                    "type": "image",
                    "assetId": "exp06-decoder-simulation-waveform",
                    "caption": "Simulation waveform for 3:8 Decoder: only one output bit Yi is high for each input combination across all 8 input values.",
                    "role": "simulation-screenshot"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "From the simulation waveform, the output bits Yi exactly match the expected outputs from the truth table for every input combination. It can also be verified that only 1 bit of Y is high in all cases, which is the defining characteristic of a decoder."
                }
            ]
        },
