        "conclusion": {
            "id": "conclusion",
            "title": "Conclusion",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "In this experiment, the implementation of a 3:8 decoder on the FPGA board was successfully completed. Both software simulation and hardware implementation were performed and verified. The simulation results matched the expected outputs from the truth table, confirming the proper functionality of the implementation. The one-hot output behaviour was clearly demonstrated on the hardware, with the active LED shifting from Y0 to Y7 as the binary input incremented from 0 to 7. The Verilog `case` statement provided an efficient and clear method for describing the decoder logic."
                }
            ]
